# Timeouts

- **Request timeout:** Use `.timeout(Duration.ofSeconds(30))` (or `config().httpClient(...)`) when the API can be slow. Avoid defaulting to very long timeouts so failures are detected quickly.
- **Connection timeout:** Configure separately if needed for "connection refused" vs "read timeout" clarity. Rest Assured uses the same HTTP client config for both when set.
- **CI vs local:** Use the same timeout values in CI and locally so flakiness is consistent; increase only when the API contract justifies it.
- **No sleep:** Prefer explicit timeouts over `Thread.sleep()`; use polling or webhook-style tests only when the API design requires it.
